Software Skills:
1. Used Procreate for sketching scenes and illustrations
2. Used Illutrator for Illustrations
3. Used After Effects for creating scenes
OnShape CAD Modelling:
Conducted a case study to design a private reading space on OnShape CAD Modelling tool which would accommodate one person and be placed indoors for student to work. One constraints was that there would be no additional lighting within the pod and privacy was maintained with walls.
Tool and Techniques:
This study was performed to investigate the design of a pod where no artificial lighting is incorporated. Sketches came in handy while choosing the overall design. Sketches were drawn with Three Iteration design model where I chose three different shapes and iterated each of them while combining the new results with the older design.
Design Process:
Started with 3 different shapes to explore overall design and finalized triangle as primary shape and sphere to add imbalance. Explored rounded corners at entrance for visual continuity. With a final design on ready on Procreate, designed the space on OnShape CAD software and made a physical model using cardboard.
Challenges and design solutions:
  1. Initial triangle sketches caused visual distraction and uneasiness which hindered the calm ambiance.
    Solution: Added more rounded forms in the design.

  2. Required to add a desk within the pod for user to keep their stuff within the restricted space.
    Solution: Designed a movable table to alter space as per user requirement.
Learning Outcomes:
  1. Learning the isometric sketching method.
  2. First experience with CAD Modelling technique.
  3. Approach various design problems wile keeping user interaction with a physical space in mind.
Sketch Breakdown:
In the sketches, it is visible that I had to incorporate constraints about privacy and artifical lighting. Sketches are fundamental to landing a project as I can often have multiple iterations to choose from. The final form also included a physical model made out of cardboard which helps to visualize the space better.
